none: Chŏnwŏn (pasture) is the third collection of novellas by An Hoe-nam (1910-?), written during the last years of Japanese colonization and the liberation space. Includes thirteen novellas by the author. The manuscripts were kept by Yi Yuk-sa (1904-1944), a poet and independent activist, passed onto leftist critique Yi Wŏn-jo (1909-1955) at Yi Yuk-sa's death-bed, and were returned to the author to be published. Cover design by Chŏng Hyŏn-ung.

seo.title: Chŏnwŏn: ch'angjakchip (short stories) / Chonwon: ch'angjakchip - Untitled
